reviews.text: I did a wedding here as Justice of the Peace. A very beautiful seting.
Great place for a quiet walk and good views of the water.  Though dogs are not allowed,  many people ignore the signs completely.
Have been coming here since I was a little boy. I've kept the tradition going at least a few times per year. So peaceful and relaxing no matter what time of year you visit.

Lovely view of the Wachusett Reservoir. Great place to take photos and have a picnic. Very peaceful please. Open year round from sunrise to sunset. Due to the  reservoir being used for public drinking no wading, swimming, or boating of any kind allowed. Fishing is acceptable.
Beautiful church provides excellent backdrop for photos. A nice place to spend an hour.

It was cold rainy day when we visited, but it was such a fun and educational experience. I took my 11 and 6 year old nieces and they thoroughly enjoyed it! The gem collection is stunning and seeing all of the fossils is so interesting. They also have a scavenger hunt for the kids, and get to take home a gem themselves. I’d definitely recommend visiting here. For old or young!

This is a wonderful little geology museum with some great collections. Entrance is free but donations gladly accepted and appreciated. There are trails outside with an interesting variety of plants and a little pond with lilies and frogs. A great place for families. There's a small gift shop right inside the museum. Friendly staff and a scavenger hunt for kids to help explore the museum. Great place!!
Great family place!   There is lots too look at.  Loved the blacklight room with the glowing rocks. So much too see and read!
One of my sons most favorite spots in the botanical garden.

This is a great geology and paleontology exhibit nestled inside of the gated of Clemson's Botanical gardens. Free entry through the gift shop. Excellent displays. An amazing Floirescent gem stone room. Plenty of things to touch. Good for young kids for about 15-20 minutes. Adults could spend 30 minutes to an hour. Interesting Desert garden out front.
Interesting and informative. Hats off to Clemson University for restoring this part of history!!
Very educational and best place to be if you want to spend time with your family
Great example of an early plantation house. Good tour. Free.
Very historic, learning  about history on how the people  lived.
If you like historical houses and items this is a great place to go to. Plus it is free ....

Absolutely Beautiful Gardens! Went late December and while obviously more dormant, a few camellias still sported their beautiful pink flowers. Excellent variety of evergreen trees and shrubs. I loved hiking through the different ecosystems and reading the many explanatory boards. Would love to come back in spring!
I've been many times. These are beautiful gardens with a lot to do. I love the rock museum and desert themed area.
A nice house with a gift shop area on the first floor and beautiful art work on the second floor, as well as a cute little library!

I have been coming here for around 30 years, its been my go.to place to recieve healing from nature, to have quick lunch during work hrs, a wonderful place to share bonding time and create memories with my grandchildren, and other friends and family, the place my bf made some very special photos of my.precious furbaby near the end of his life then the last outing with her as me, her and her husband and I spent hours making and posing for about a 1000 pictures. Thanks to everyone who invested in making CBG a beautiful part of my life.
12/30/18  We visit often and enjoy nature, very nicely set up. Dog owners pay no attention to no pet areas tho and kids make LOTS of noise, lack of parenting.

This place is incredible. I thought my home team up north was big, but this surpasses it. The entire campus is just beautiful. My family and I even drove about mile from the main campus to their Botanical Gardens. I is just wonderful! We are going back in the spring when the plants are in bloom.
Very nice facility. Even as a non Clemson fan I appreciate the fan passion and environment. If you like college football, this is a good place to check out

What a great stadium and college football experience.  The stadium is great and even up in the upper deck you can see the game.  Definitely show up early so you can watch the Tigers walk and see all the players and you don't want to miss the entrance at the beginning of the game where they come down the hill next to Howard's rock!  The whole experience is full of excitement.

Nice stadium, but you have to leave to get from the upper deck to the lower part.  We wanted to move down in the late part of a blowout for a better view.  Getting out of the parking lots after the game is a whole different story, 0 stars for that.

Was there for the Wake Forest Game, my daughter is IN Daniel High School JROTC...they were doing the Color Guard for the game...the stadium was nice...lots of seats, BUT screen to see the action even if you couldn't see very well...Food and Drinks available, restrooms were clean...we had a good time...GO TIGERS!!! Hope you enjoy your time spent there...they know how to entertain!!!

It was our first time to visit.  We have gone by it when we go to watch Clemson football but its usually to late when we go back.  We got the Deep Dish and it was great. Will try to stop again.  They have a salad bar also. [Chicago style]

Amazing original style pizza. The owner is great and been making pizza for 35 years! Pizza places like these are so rare and the quality is top notch. Go support this long standing Clemson business. You will not be disappointed!
Pizza is really good. Chicago style with all the toppings you want. Highly recommend the atlas 28", with 3 toppings feeds 8 college guys with some to-go, for like $5 each ±tip.
Great service & a really awesome , large party pizza. The sweet tea was great, as well. I will be back.
Nice place for pizza and a salad reasonably priced

Great Diner food with very fair prices. I have enjoyed eating here and the food is exactly what you'd expect from a classic American diner. The restaurant is quite small, but has nice decorations and you can tell it's a staple of the community. Remember to bring cash however, as cards were not accepted at the time that I went.
Been feasting on double cheeseburger plates here at Mac's for about 50 years.  Always a pleasure to come back.  Good Clemson folks and cheeseburgers and sweet tea like none other.
Cool place good atmosphere mediocre food

The prebreaded frozen fried chicken that was still cold in the center when served was interesting.... I liked the Catsup on the fries tho. There's something suspiciously wrong with all the 4 and 5 star ratings. I thought Clemson only accepted smart or rich kids????
Ate there for lots of years. Still good today.
